project: Be George Of Mice And Men
Of Mice And Men : About Lennie

Lennie is one of the main characters in the novel Of Mice And Men written by John Steinbeck. He is very strong and can't realise how much he can hurt someone. So, when he pets a mouse or a puppy, he ends up killing it. However, Lennie is very nice and won't hurt anybody but unwillingly.
Lennie is mentally ill. He acts and thinks just like a child. He's obsessed with soft things. That is the reason why he often gets into troubles because people can't understand his behavior.

Luckily, Lennie is looked after by his good friend George. George and he are travelling all around the country during the Great Depression. George doesn't have any mental desorders so he can teach Lennie how to fit in the society. Lennie always obeys George.
Lennie is my favorite character in the novel Of Mice And Men for several reasons.

First of all: I find his innocence moving. He is just as pure as a child. He doesn't understand racism, discriminations or hate. He's too kind for this sick and racist world. He is simple, loving and sweet, as I said above : just like children. I always loved children  so I can only feel compassion for Lennie.

Also, Lennie is really funny ! He says a lot of inappropriate things in any context without realising how funny it is ! When he deals with his dreams (having a little land with his friend George, having rabbits...) he becomes very funny because his wills are completely unachievable (like having blue, red or green rabbits) but he claims it just like it was allready real !

To sum up, I think this is the reason why Lennie is so endearing: Lennie is the reflection of every nice side of each human being. He is innocent, funny and nice. He might be awkward but at last, he's the loveliest charater in this book. We all should try to be as nice as Lennie and if everybody were, Lennie wouldn't have been killed. So, to pay tribut to Lennie, here is a rainbow rabbit. His name is Alfalfa.
